reviews: Stayed from April 20-24 I was very impressed with this hotel. It is a small boutique type hotel. Rooms are nice and clean, employee are very nice and accommodating. My daughter and I could see the top of the Eiffel Tower from our room. Would definitely stay there again.

Perfect little hotel with great service by the receptionist Valerie who made sure we got a perfect overnight stay with a lively view and as Meliá member we got a cute macaroons! Hotel could do a bit of Reno but it,s also a time capsule experience. Thank you

I have stayed at other Meliá hotels and booked this property based on some of the positive reviews, but my stay ended up being quite disappointing. Unfortunately this was one of the worst hotels I’ve stayed at recently, specifically:
- Rooms were very tired and in desperate need of renovation
- Bathroom was in dire state with poor hairdryer and water leaks
- Team were mostly friendly but simply not professional and do not seem to care
- They did not have a wine bottle opener (this is France!)

The only saving grace is the great location

Amazing stay - the staff went the extra mile to make our stay special and gave us a great room, decorated for our special celebration, along with wine and macaroons. We were made to feel really special and are so delighted we chose to stay here. Shoutout to Said from Reception who went the extra mile!

Lovely, professional service, friendly, helpful reception team and great location.
Nice, clean, spacious room and bathroom.
We were very impressed.
My mum felt really special when she saw her birthday cake & letter left for her.
Great service.

Pros
Friendly and helpful staff (recommending places to eat & ordering taxis).
Good location close to sites.
Nice hotel lobby.
Beautiful and spacious bathroom.
Nice teas and coffee provided.

…..
Cons
Room smelt of cigarettes when first entered had to open all windows.
Rooms & corridors could do with a refurb.
Walls thin, could hear noises from neighbouring rooms all night.
Shower changes between hot and cold.
No shower cap.
No iron in room (although note, you can book an ironing service the night before for a fee).
Internet signal bad on laptop.
Breakfast room too small for amount of people (I would suggest that they stagger the times that guests go for breakfast).
Room service for dinner advertised but not offered.

My stay here was ok. But for the fact that basic things were not met, and also given the price, I have to rate it below average.

The room was tiny. The shower was terrible- either hot or cold. The towels were also very tired. Wifi was good and also the location is good.

I wouldn’t really stay in this hotel again on a business trip. I had to stay here as Paris is booming and not much choice.

No sound proofing at all, extremely noisy. And no sleep for us with a party starting at 3 am above our room. No working air conditioning. Should have been started today but still not working this evening. Not possible to open the windows because of the loud traffic day and night.
We moved to another room supposedly with less noise. Now we have a bathtub that is not draining and noise.
Horrible hotel.

Excellent location near Victor Hugo metro. Safe, comfortable area. Rooms are fine if small but it is what you expect in Paris. Good value for what it was. Everyone was welcoming. It was comfortable and as a solo traveler I felt safe!

We stayed at this lovely hotel for a 4 night City Break. Check in and out was quick and easy and we were made most welcome by the Reception staff who were helpful and pleasant. Beautifully clean and warm and the beds were so comfortable we were able to get a good nights sleep ready to explore the next day. Breakfast was excellent with plenty of variety. Perfectly situated for a City break. Restaurants near to the hotel were good too. Will definitely return in the future.

Arrived early to the hotel and concierge was very welcoming and helpful in storing our bags. Check-in was swift and easy. Room was spotless and so comfortable. We were fortunate to have a balcony and street view. The bathroom was warm which allowed for a steamy shower and our towels to dry very quickly. We were greeted by the friendly staff every time we entered and left the hotel. Our check out was very simple, the city tax was very reasonable too. Will definitely stay here again thanks to location, ease and enjoyability.

The staff was welcoming, specially for Paris.

The room, despite getting an upgrade to a large room, was dated. Everything felt old.

There where no USB or USC chargers, hardly any milk for coffee or tea.

The bathroom was is serious need of revamp.

It could have been a frustrating hosting experience (water temperature regulator not working, lack of water in the shower and leftover food in the refrigerator), thanks to the manager Rodrigo who upgraded to a premium room plus a souvenir, the experience it became bearable.

Everything you want from a city hotel. Friendly staff. Lovely room. Great location. Room rate very reasonable. Convenient for the metro - just 20 mins to Gare du Nord if travelling by Eurostar. Very close to Arc de Triomphe and Champs Elysee.

I picked this hotel because I have stayed a number of times at the Melia in Granada and have always been satisfied. The Melia Champs Elysees, I found to be better and the location is very good for all the tourist attractions and the Metro. On this occasion I was visiting Paris with my daughters for a weekend break. I booked two rooms, a double and a twin. On arrival we were greeted by the very friendly and helpful reception personnel. Both rooms, were of a reasonable size and exceptionally clean. Yes, the bathrooms are small, but very clean and well equipped with hairdryer, ample soap, shampoo, conditioner and towels. Yes the room is noisy if you have the window open, but the noise of the city didn't bother me. The hotel is a short walk from the Metro and quite close to it there are also some decent restaurants for dinner, lunch or breakfast. It is many years since I have stayed in Paris, it's not a city I know well, but I was really happy with my choice of hotel in the main due the staff, cleanliness and the location and I would definitely stay again.

We selected this hotel last minute, we expected small rooms as noted in other reviews but they were very very small and the bathrooms are tiny, You need to move around sideways. Worse is the noise, you can hear every single noise on the hallway and every car passing outside. Staff were very friendly and helpful but the hotel needs some serious work. Basic amenities are in the room and there's a coffee and tea station. The hotel is in a quiet area with very few restayrants/bars nearby, it's far from most attractions, it takes 15-20 minutes by taxi to everything except arc de triomphe.

Comfy bed, bathroom in amazing marble, few kind of high quality tea...
excellent Hotel position near Arc de Triomphe and Tour Eiffel.
Sympathic and kind receptionist Javier :)
thank You Melia staff, we enjoyed our stay

The location was good, 15 min walk to Champs Elysées or trocadero. The room size was correct comparing to other hotels in Paris, but it was old, wooden door was rotten, the bathroom is very small and there is a towel heater knob that you can easily bump into while using the toilet. The room was overheated, and very noisy, the door is not soundproof. The price is high comparing to the facilities the hotel offers. A good thing to mention is that the bed and pillows were comfortable.

It was out of this world, awesome experience. On Monday October 14, I took a red eye flight from D.C. to Paris, by the time, I got to the hotel I was extremely tired, frustrated, etc. At the desk Layla, listened to my concerns, she was extremely helpful, polite, and professional. I had a friend in Paris that I was unable to connect with using my phone. Layla dialed the number from her desk phone and I was able to talk to my friend. Throughout my six nights at the hotel Layla was there for any assistance with utmost friendliness and professionalism. In response, I bought flowers for the front desk. Sqio Ainouche was also ready to assist and help in friendly manner engaging in conversation related to my stay in Paris.
Rodrigo was always there for anything to make me feel at home. On Monday October 21, 2019, I filled my car rental gas tank for 84 Euros; my credit cards were declined, I had no money to pay. I called the hotel and Rodrigo came to the gas station with 84 Euros.
Everyone working at the hotel was there to make everyone staying at the hotel feel at home. All three bellmen were extremely helpful and friendly. Two men working the graveyard shift (11 pm -7 am), were friendly and assisted me throughout my stay, if I needed anything.
The entire restaurant staff always greeted with pleasant smiles and always asked me how they can be of any assistance.
I felt like I was in my own house; everyone working at the hotel were there with pleasant smiles and greetings; satisfying good

Pleasant friendly staff felt satisfying experience

The staff was friendly, helpful and professional. The gave excellent directions to get around the city of Paris. The hotel was located in an area that was excellent for shopping and site seeing. We enjoyed our stay at this hotel.

I was there only one night. The hotel is nice and really well located. Unfortunately, it’s very old and needs a huge renovation. Specially the bathroom: broken and very low shower, low water pressure, no glass to avoid water coming out -not a huge problem as the water pressure is low-,... my room was a superior king room, so the size was great, but I saw a standard room and they were pretty small (if you are 2 people, I would recommend to pay for the superior).
Very nice employees at reception. Good service.

Really a glam city. Wonderful parks. Excellent gastronomy. Beautiful museums. Special places. Unfortunately people are arrogant, but some people said this is cultural behaviour. However, the city shines a lot.

This cozy, small hotel is in a great location close the nice restaurants, metro etc. The rooms are nicely appointed but everything is tight. The bathroom is updated and nice. The buffet breakfast is very good with many standard options.

We had a lovely stay. The hotel is conveniently located to the metro, eateries and shopping. The breakfast had many options and was delicious. We never felt rushed or hurried. The room & bath were compact but comfortable. The bath is appointed with quality amenities and a hair dryer. My only ?? comment was the main elevator was out and the charming little elevator that ran up through the spiral stairway was a little spotty in operation. That said, repair service was on it quickly.

Starting at the arrival, we had a room in the 4th floor and the Hotel elevator was broken, the second day the door knob broke and got scrambled the digital system and no one in the Hotel were able to open the door. I was paying above 300 Euros per night in a hotel that does not not worth 50 euros per night

Great staff and hospitality. I appreciate the lady at the front desk finding a private ride for us to go to Disney. They were quick to help me with all my needs. Location was perfect and within walking distance of all major shopping.

The staff is very helpful, attentive and thoughtful. Rooms are very well cleaned, nice and quiet. Location is just perfect, close to Champs Elysees and Eifel Tour. I will definitely stay at Melia Paris on my next trip.

Quiet, clean, small hotel near Pl Victor Hugo, and Metro, 10 mins walk from Champs Elysées, 15 mins from Trocadero.

Lift broke down during our stay, which meant getting to the sixth floor room (605) a chore. Room was just big enough for two adults but needs drawer space for clothes. Breakfast got crowded but was well serviced. Thinnest towels in the bathroom of any 4* hotel I've stayed in. Regular double rooms vary significantly in size but 605 is fine. Very firm beds a double plus.

Excellent hotel. Great breakfast with a wide choice of food. Room spacious especially for Paris. Highlight of the hotel was undoubtedly the staff, who were all friendly and helpful. Would definitely recommend.

Had a great stay for a night and the staff were very helpful. I had checked out early in the morning but could back in again for a few more hours as my meeting was delayed!
The location is close to the centre of the town, walking distance to everywhere

I stayed there for 2 nights. Staff were very nice and friendly, spoke multiply languages. Breakfast was amazing. The room was very cosy just a bit small. Good location as well. Would definitely stay again.
There should be some complimentary waters in the room on arrival. Also, would have been nice to have smaller pillows.

Convenient & safe location. Walking distance to restaurants, shops & Metro. Clean, spacious rooms & bathroom. Comfortable bed. Enjoyed breakfast & the expresso. Awesome staff! Awesome stay! Will definitely be returning. Thank you!

We couldn’t have been more pleased with our accommodations and the most helpful staff. They made us feel at home and even put special sweet treats in our room one night! We had two rooms as we were traveling with our daughter and granddaughter and when we arrived we were on different floors, Virginia checked and changed it and got the same floor. The rooms have been remodeled and were very well appointed. Their room was very spacious, ours was quite adequate with a smaller bathroom, but we had 2 front windows. We were there 4 nights. We walked everywhere, the metro was close by but we weren’t familiar with using it, so we opted to walk, which for Parisians wouldn’t have been considered far. There were cafes everywhere and all were good. I had trouble trying to print our boarding passes and the nicest man on the reception (I neglected to get his name) had worked a 24 hour shift couldn’t have been more helpful. Everyone was wonderful! Definitely would recommend.

We truly enjoyed our experience at this hotel. The location is incredible. You are essentially in the middle of short walks to the Eiffel, Arc De Triomph, Champs Elysees and metro stations as well as multiple cafe's and great shops right in the same vicinity as the hotel! Drive from the airport was also nice, about 40 mins. We absolutely loved the boutique style and character of this hotel and the staff - some of the best I've encountered. They go above and beyond to serve and ensure you are well taken care of and are very kind and courteous. In addition, we got some great guidance from Chris as we were planning out a few day trips to certain sites, he was awesome! I would definitely stay here again and thank the staff for their hospitality during our trip!

Paris is a fantastic place to visit. Instill cant believe I was in paris, but It was an awesome trip. The staff was beyond awesome. Beyond awesome! The trip was in a great neighborhood and I felt like I was French for a week.

Nice room and good service but having the shower without warm water and lots of dust on the door was absolutely not expected for this level of hotel. I did not have breakfast but colleagues said it was very good.

I arrived at the hotel at 10 am after a long flight, and they went the extra mile to try and find me a room, so I was able to catch up on sleep right away. I really appreciated it.

Hotel is a block away from Victor Hugo station, and within walking distance to the Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triomphe, etc.

Quiet hotel within the city. Good breakfast. I was very satisfied with the level of customer service.

Location is great. The service is fantastic. I had a great time in this hotel. The rooms are cozy, bed is comfortable and bathroom is huge. Nothing to complain about. Nice restaurants and cafes around.

Staff are really nice and friendly- very kind!!!!Breakfast is good as they promote it. WiFi is working.
Bar is closing 10:30 pm.
Rooms are definitely old, not looking like on website. needed renovation ages ago:(
I am not sure of competition and can you get something better for the price in this location. Hope this helped.

perfect location for exploring Paris, we went racing for the weekend at Auteuil so it was a 5 min taxi ride away, you can walk to the Eiffel tower of champs Elysses easily with the metro close by as well, there are excellent restaurants a stones throw away too, the rooms are large and nice bathrooms, although you are in the centre of Paris you cannot hear much traffic , The staff are the best thing about this hotel, they were very welcoming and helpful, on Sunday their phone lines were down so also the wifi, the receptionist leant me her phone so i could use her data as I had a problem with my phone , extremely kind of her. I would stay there again definitely !

Nice hotel, great location , breakfast expensive so didn't bother, bar and mini bar expensive too. Should water in rooms be free?I would have expected that in a 4 star hotel. Overall one of the better hotels i have stayed in, in Paris

Situated at tge centre , with walking distance to Eiffel, MELIA is my go to property when in paris . For me the location was the key with the transportation and tube at stones throw distance and surrounded with lot of restaurant, Pharmacies and super stores.

The staff was extremely helpful! We do not speak French & were nervous but the desk personnel explained & helped with directions, menus, transportation & other questions even not related to hotel. Would stay here again!

I had the wonderful pleasure of staying at the Melia - Champs Elysees on my 50th birthday trip. Rooms very cozy and clean. The hotel staff was accommodating, polite and friendly. I had a room facing the courtyard, the view was what I would love to see looking out of my Paris window. The (lifts) are quite small. I also loved the location of the hotel. There are several restaurants, grocery store, shops, boutiques, pastry shops and even a McDonalds and Starbucks within 5 minutes walking. Overall, I was charmed, and our stay was wonderful.

Well situated for Metro and within walking distance of Arc De Triumph. Nice area but restaurants in area pricey compared to some other areas we ate in. Hotel staff friendly and helpful. Refurbishment going on in some rooms but this did not spoil our stay. Air conditioning not working in April which would have been useful first 2 days of stay when it was hot.

well located hotel, small and friendly. good buffet breakfast, but get there too late as bacon / cooked elements etc will may have already been snapped up by earlier eaters. staff very friendly and helpful at all times and hotel clean and tidy. we stayed in Premium rooms, but the both mine and my daughters room had some deficiency in the bathrooms (shower holder broken so you couldn't stand under the shower you had to hold it an try to was at the same time, or jacuzzi bath not working in daughters room). the issues above were not the end of the world but were disappointing and not worth paying premium rates, possibly better going for cheaper rooms if you stay.

First of all, the name should not mislead you. This hotel is not on the Champs Elysees although it is close by. I arrived in the late evening and I was welcomed by a very friendly receptionist. She completed the check in process very fast and I was heading to my room. My first shock was at the elevator. It was almost impossible for two persons to squeeze into the elevator without touching each other. That was helpful to manage my expectations before entering my room which turned out to be also very tiny. There was almost no space even to open my luggage. Otherwise, the room was very clean and tidy. At night it was relatively cold. I turned on the heating system. But there was a noise like a steam engine working. Hence I switched off the heating system in order to have a comfortable sleep.

If you are going to spend most of your time outside of the hotel and looking for a central location in Paris, this may be the right place for you.

This is an amazing hotel by all means. The location is just perfect, just a few steps away from subway and bus lines, and a few minutes walk to Arc de Triumph, Champs Elysees, and Eiffel Tower. Highly attentive, capable and helpful staff with lots of smiling faces. All our requests were met literally in a minute. We booked a Premium Room, a big wow! Very large, spacious, fully equipped and comfortable room, even with a walk-in closet for clothes and luggage. Huge bathroom with high-end amenities. Incredible housekeeping, one of the best I have seen. Delicious open buffet breakfast. Walls are a bit thin but guests were alright I guess, we had entirely silent, calm and serene nights. I guess this was an old city hotel which was bought by Melia and renovated into a beautiful crossover between traditional and modern. Loved all five days that we spent here. Melia eventually became my favorite hotel chain in recent years, and this hotel is no exception. Melia Paris Champs Elysees will definitely be our home for our succeeding Paris trips as well. Kudos!

Lovely hotel with good sized rooms walking distance to Notre Dame. Classic decor unlike some of the hotels in Paris, with crisp white sheets and towels. Good sized bathroom. Breakfast continental style with lots of choices. Hotel staff welcoming and helpful.

We were staying at Paris first time during summer 2018. We chose Melia because of my former experience staying at Melia-hotel in London. Hotel was nice and rooms were spacious and bathroom did an impression. Hotel location was good, because of metro and sightseeing. Service was helpful and welcoming, they also mentioned that champs elysees was an expensive area to stay in and that we noticed. I had the most expensive gin&tonic of my life at the hotel bar but backyard of the hotel was nice to enjoy the drink. We slept well here and without disturbing noises!

I stayed here for 2 nights on business. Check in was easy and my bag was taken up. I have to say the passenger lift was the most compact lift I have ever seen before but this was expected as its modified for the building. My room was on the second floor and to my surprise this was quite compact also.

However for a business trip this was fine. The bed was comfy and met my needs. The morning breakfast was standard and expected the usual. All in all the hotel is fine for business but may be difficult to serve any other purpose.

I stayed here while I attended Paris fashion week. The hotel is very centrally located and close to most of the venues that shows are normally held at. The service is great. The staff is friendly and sincere. My room was clean and comfortable and luxurious. It was a great place to return to after a long day. Everything touristy is also located very close to the hotel. The price was fair and because I book with Melia often and I am a member of the Melia rewards program I got a free room upgrade which was fabulous. I can not comment on the breakfast because I never did go for breakfast. But I would book here again.

Very clean and comfortable room. Great location, very close to the Arch De Triumph. Staff were very attentive and friendly. Would highly recommend this hotel and will definitely stay there again on my next trip to Paris.

The hotel is located in a beautiful building close to objectives of interest. Rooms are spacious, well decorated, with very comfortable beds, breakfast very ok. The furniture unfortunately it is quite scarce. Excellent staff! One over another, i will definitively come back!

I’ve been coming to this little hotel for several decades - well before it was bought by Melia. It is classed as a 4-star and maybe by the strict tick-box approach of the Ministry of Tourism it is. But it isn't. It needs to smarten itself up. And take a more client-orientated approach. Some rooms are tired. Ours 607 has a shower bath which is frankly perilous unless you're an acrobat. The coffee on offer in the room is bog standard Nescafe. A Magimix coffee maker? And then there's the water issue. It should supply two free bottles a day. It's mini-bar water is €4.50!!. For 275ml. So - in order to earn its 4 stars it needs to improve. Staff as always helpful.

Lovely location, beautiful hotel! Rooms are fantastic, very good size, tastefully decorated with very comfortable beds. We found everything we were looking for, excellent staff, excellent place to stay!

Loved the location. Easy access to the Metro and even walking distance (20 minutes) to Foundation Louis Vuitton. Felt that the street was safe and liked the variety of shops and restaurants close by. Big thanks to a wonderful staff who were always friendly. Biggest applause to housekeeping. What an absolute pleasure it was to return to my impeccably tidied room after a long day of excursions.

The hotel is conveniently located in a beautiful building in the heart of Avenue Victor Hugo. The rooms are spacious by Paris standards, well decorated, the service is good and the staff are friendly. I will definitively come back!

Everything was perfect: hotel’s location, variety of the food during breakfast, very nice rooms, good services, staff’s flexibility.. Highly recomended hotel!!!Thank you for the warm welcome and stay!

Quiet location in lively area (restaurants, shops). Friendly and efficient staff. Perfect breakfast buffet. Comfortable rooms and bathrooms. A good place to be while exploring the many attractive places in Paris.

Very nice and clean hotel, nice location next to the city center and metro stations. Good breakfast,friendly personnel, beautiful and cozy room! I would definitely recommend it for couples, families or business travel!

We recently stayed four nights at this very mediocre hotel. The only positive was its location to the subway and to the Champs Elysees. However, I would never recommend this hotel. Check in took a long time. The clerk was dishonest about how much breakfast cost. He quoted us a figure. When we said we weren't interested he lowered the price slightly. The one morning I did pay for breakfast (20 euro), I was very disappointed in the quality and the selection. Our room was very tiny. It was also very hot so we had to sleep with both windows open. The bed was very hard, as were the pillows, so I barely slept. The furniture was old and beaten up. The coffeemaker didn't work properly and had instant coffee. The bathroom was cramped with no air flow. Not even the toiletries smelled good. The hotel seemed neglected. I had a miserable stay.

Our first room had a broken AC, second room had cigarette smoke. After 2 days and no sleep, moved to a beautiful room in the back of the property with no issues. For the record, we travel a lot and never complain. We’ve also stayed at several melia properties and have never had an issue. But when you’re paying this much for a week in Paris, rooms need to be up to par. Beautiful hotel and great location, staff was ok. If the hotel enforced its nonsmoking policy and updated their AC, it would be a great property.

Overall good experience. Room is good enough for my need. Very clean. Breakfast is simple yet fantastic. Location is convenient. Victo Hugo Metro is very close by and some of the Paris attractions such as Eiffel Tower, Trocadero is within walking distance. If you have a meeting at OECD, it is a walking distance as well. (about 15 minutes walk).

Our first visit to a Melia Hotel was excellent. From the entry/front desk reception to our departure, everything was wonderful. Very accommodating, responsive, friendly staff, coupled with feeling of historic ambiance in the hotel property. Location was excellent for metro, site-seeing, dining, and shopping. We'll be sure to book again if returning to Paris.

Everything was great: location , breakfast, reservation, staff, and especially bed comfort and the good smells. Pamper yourself at Melia Hotel Champs ElyseesRecommended hotelI really enjoyed my stay in Paris and for sure I will advise all the customers to try the service of Melia Champs Elysees :) .

located 5 -10 mins walk from Arc de Triomphe and 10 mins walk from Trocadero & another 5 to Eiffel Tower. metro 2 mins walk and bus stops on Place nearby and bus routes to pretty much everywhere across Paris. hotel has good atmosphere, good quality breakfast with reasonable degree of choice and very friendly staff. a few niggles, including in room safe not working (and not fixed during the stay - shame) but worked around these and had a very enjoyable stay. if you are looking to be in this part of Paris definitely check out this hotel.

My family and I got 3 rooms (5 of us ). We checked in early and one room was not ready . We all got the same type (premium) and paid the same amount. The one room were told would be ready at 2pm. We filled out the paperwork and left our bags and went out for the day. We returned at 6:30pm and I was given a key for a room (215). Went upstairs and the key did not work so went back downstairs and the porter got new keys and went back up and got in the room and people were in there! And I might add was way smaller than the premium rooms the rest of my family were in! They then gave me a key for another room 115 again a much smaller room. Went back down again and the man at the front desk said oh I am sorry I am going to upgrade you to the nicest room we have , and gave me a key to room 601 (that is the room my brother and sister in law was in) !!! He then said this is your room as it has your name on it and I said no that is my brothers name! He kept insisting that was the type of room I chose. I explained to him we all chose the same type of room except one we wanted the two separate beds. Keep in mind all the beds are two separate beds it’s just they either push them together or apart. Also the premium rooms I was told were at the back . The room 115 is at the front so no sleep for me getting to listen to all the people and traffic on the street. Also if he was upgrading my room why was he giving me the original he gave my brother? They also had champagne and some cookies in my room. I don’t drink alcohol!!! I would think twice before staying here again. When I asked for an adjustment he said I will need to talk to the manager in the morning. It’s going to be a loong night. So spoke with the manager Manuel. He was very pleasant and understanding. He asked the other gentleman if i was in a standard room and he said no premium. At first he offered me free breakfast...um no thanks...40 euros off the bill....um no thanks...i then offered him to come upstairs and see i didn't even sleep in the bed as it was so noisy and the bathroom door didn't even open and close and the handle was all screwed up. He finally offered half off the room and i insisted on a late check out. He agreed so i was satisfied. If staying here avoid room 115 at all costs.

This is an "Excellent location" near the Arc de Triomphe. The Melia has a very attentive staff and excellent breakfast! Rooms are clean and have a very comfortable bed. The hotel can be a little hard to find because the signage is very small. I would likely choose to stay at this hotel again the next time I am in Paris

We were in Paris celebrating our 56th weeding anniversary. The weather was very pleasant a bit on the cool side compared to Barcelona whee we also spent time celebrating. The hotel is centrally located in a very nice area with nice restaurants and stores for shopping. Hotel is within walking distance to the metro, Effie Towel, the Camps Elysee and area to catch Hop-On and Hop-Off tour buses. The staff was very polite, courteous, and very helpful. Once we returned from dinner, a complimentary bottle of Champlain on ice with two glasses awaited us to celebrate our anniversary. I highly recommend this facility.

Very conveniently located near Metro station which takes you to the Arc de Triomphe in one stop. If you like to walk, the Arc and Champ Elysee are in good walking distance. Our room on the 6th floor street side gave us a spectacular view of the Eiffel Tower, especially when lit up at night.The room was quite large with comfortable king size bed.What made our 6 night stay most enjoyable was the helpful and friendly attitude of the staff, especially the porters Mr.Tiss and Mr. Gopal. The front desk people were also very helpful.We enjoyed having an espresso or a drink in the back garden in the evening. Of our three visits to Paris this was the best hotel experience.

We chose the Melia Champs Elysee after staying at a Melia Hotel in Milan earlier in the year and expecting a similar level of quality. Unfortunately we were very disappointed.Whilst the location is good and the staff are very helpful the Hotel itself is, in my opinion, nowhere near the 4 star rating it claims.The rooms are incredibly small and the ensuite bathroom virtually unusable unless you are a lot small and thinner than I am. I would have been less critical of the room sizes had they been reflected in the price but it wasn't a cheap hotel so I would have expected better.Positives:- Location and helpful staff.Negatives: Price and room sizes.

Boutique hotel. Excellent location!!! Everything was near. Metro station is 2 min away. Friendly and helpful staff. Rooms are very clean. Breakfast is excellent. We will come back. Thank you Melia, you made our stay outstanding, as always!!!

We stayed at this hotel through an Easyjet package holiday.
On arrival we were quickly checked in by a pleasant member of staff. Our bedroom was clean and smelt fresh and was kept that way all week. There is a very good buffet style breakfast with a good selection of food on offer. Front desk staff are very good at arranging bookings or tours. At the top of the avenue there is access to the metro which is easy to use if you get the Ratpf blue backed metro map which shows all stops nearest tourist attractions. We got ours in Gare du Nord but they're most likely available in any metro ticket office.
This was our first time in Paris and this Hotel. When I return again I will definitely stay here.

The experience here was great.Juan Carlos was really helpful when our safe would not open.he tried his very best until we remembered the number!Very close to all the important attractions and close proximity to Gare du NordWill definitely come back.

The staff was over friendly.
It was super clean.
And
The location is amazing.
Best way to reach there was metro. I got down at victor Hugo.
After a day long walk, a hot water tub bath was relaxing.
Hotel has amazing sweets at the reception. I always used to pick up one or two while leaving or entering the hotel.

Nice and cozy hotel at Triangle D’Or - Paris with a worth cost. This is the best place to Stay if You like to be close to fancy restaurants and the most iconic monuments and Museuns in Paris. I had a warm welcome by the friendly staff. Breakfast was really good. I certainly Will come back.

Great location. Easy to get around and metro is close by.

Restaurants near by are wonderful.

Second time I’ve stayed here would stay again,

Lovely hotel. Staff extremely helpful.

Rooms are small but it’s Europe.

Really enjoyed our stay.

We spent 5 nights there recently, and it was a very positive experience. The staff was friendly and attentive. Our room was on the top floor and we could see the top half of the Eiffel Tower from our window. We highly recommend this hotel, and would definitely stay there again the next time that we are in Paris.

Spent 2 nights here and first impression was that the front of house staff were attentive and accomodating. The room was comfortable and had shutters on the outside to keep the light out and double glazing making it dark and quiet at night.
Unfortunately it was downhill from here.

The weather was hot and aircon essential. On turning it on to the lowest speed it was so noisy you couldn’t hear the tv let alone sleep with it on - then it began leaking water requiring towels underneath. Maintenance came and said nothing could be done until a weekday as no one works on weekends. (No suggestion of room change)

On Monday the leak was fixed but not the noise so had to sleep in a hot stuffy room.

Then the hairdryer on the wall only works in 5 second intervals before it cuts out. Maintenance called again, told to only use hairdryer on lowest speed (same advice for aircon that didn’t help either device). Replacement hairdryer sent up and was told to return it to reception when finished. Really? In my PJ’s?

Comfy king bed but 2 joined singles which is fine but one corner didn’t sit flat so when you sat on it, it clunked to the ground.

Very very small lift, large or unusually shaped items of luggage may not fit in it.

Overall, pleasant enough stay in a good location but requires some maintenance and hospitality attention.

The front desk staff dropped the ball with our transportation to the airport and then lied to us making us lose precious time to get to the airport and almost missing our flight. We ended up catching an Uber which arrived in one minute and cost us double than the pre-arranged transportation that was not booked.

We are loyal Melia customers. We normally go to the premium Gran Melia beach resorts. This was our first trip to a city Melia hotel.

Impressions on arrival were very good. We were upgraded to a suite on the 8th Floor with great views over the city. The hotels location is great - located close to the West Bank sites such as the Eiffel Tower.

Air conditioning was great, particularly on a very hot weekend.

Breakfast on the Saturday morning was satisfactory, but we had high expectations based on stays in Gran Melia hotels. Scrambled eggs were cold and fried eggs burned. Breakfast was somewhat better on the Sunday morning. On Monday it was good. The food selection is very good.

Throughout our stay one of the lifts was broken down. We returned exhausted after a day sightseeing to find the second lift broken too. Spoke to Reception to get an embarrassed sorry, but no idea when it would be fixed. We fought our way up eight floors to get to our room. We found this very annoying.

Later on the Sunday the second lift was fixed. But still going painfully slow and feeling like it would break down again.

Housekeeping can be a bit hit and miss. We had to ask one day, as they had missed us. The evening turn down happened once.

On balance, we had an enjoyable stay, and the room upgrade was appreciated . But the hotel needs to attend to customer service and breakfasts at weekends, and get their lifts serviced.

Love the location, in town but not too busy. My preference is that it's very close to my meeting place.
Staying at the hotel, I can find convenient transportation, i.e. taxi, metro, etc. In addition, the hotel is surrounded by shops, restaurants, coffee parlors, pharmacies, etc. Very convenient for my stay!

The location is great. Between Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe and metro. All in walking distance which gives you opportunity to "see" Paris.

Paid extra for Premium room but still seemed very small! Beds were separated to 2 twin beds as requested. Beds and pillows were comfortable. Air conditioning worked well. We were on first floor so convenient to stairs to lobby. Bathroom was spacious but sink area was cramped. Shower had half glass door so after showering, floor was always wet. Water pressure was good. Housekeeping did ok. Asked for extra towels one night because of the flooding during shower time and the they were taken away when room was cleaned. Room was quiet and curtains were helpful keeping room dark since sunset wasn't until 10:30.
I paid for the breakfast included and it was fresh, limited, great donuts and croissants. Breakfast staff was great!!

Front desk staff - Andrea and manager Rodrigo were superb!! Another desk associate gave us misinformation on our first night about getting to our Liore Valley trip the next morning which resulted in us missing our tour bus and causing us MUCH stress and loss of over $200 dollars. Andrea and Rodrigo tried VERY hard to help us out that morning!! Later that day the employee that gave us the wrong information didn't handle himself well when confronted by us and Rodrigo. I won't mention employee name because I don't think its necessary. Rodrigo and hotel management sent us champagne and macaroons the next night and paid for half the price for re-booking the Liore Valley trip!! Rodrigo really went out of his way to help us with anything we needed including giving us great train directions for getting to Palace of Versailles! Rodrigo and Andrea really helped make our trip a success!!
I would stay here again because of location if I were to ever visit Paris again!

Before I write this review, just want to BEWARE you that as told by their reception staff, they DO NOT have Queen or King beds for their Premium category rooms......... So if you plan on staying here with your spouse/partner, be prepared to sleep on 2 Twin beds joined together, otherwise they’ll ask you 120 Euro for upgrading to a junior suite. Remember, all this for a Queen bed!

Have just checked in here about an hour back and already too frustrated at the attitude of their front desk staff!

The staff was very courteous, Housekeeping was excellent and the room was very comfortable. The reception service was always very good and pleasant. The location of the hotel is superb and it was very convenient to visit places from here.

I stayed a couple of days in this hotel and was quite disappointed.
One day, they forgot to do my room and I had to request them to do it when back in the evening. Fortunately they were reactive enough to do it.
But the most incredible thing is what happened with the taxi when I checked out.
When I checked out at 7am, I order at the reception a taxi to go to the airport. The receptionist called and told me that the taxi should be there in 7 minutes which was OK with me. There were another customer waiting for a taxi which was ordered before who was also waiting. When the taxi arrived, the driver gave a a € note in a discrete manner to the receptionist. In France, taxi drivers are not supposed to bribe receptionist to get a taxi.
Then, the phone rang and the receptionist told me that the taxi will be there in 20 mins which was clearly not acceptable. When I started to get unhappy, he called the taxi stand which is 2 mins from the hotel and the taxi arrived within 3 minutes. When I asked the normal taxi driver what happened, he told me that it was a classic scheme that instead of calling normal taxis and paying the fixed 50€ price to go to the airport, receptionist call private companies and get a tip from the drivers but when the car arrives it shows already 14€ in the meter making the trip much more expensive.
I find this practice totally not acceptable and do not understand why the management is not taking action, unless they all share the tip?

The hotel is in a very god location to the elite 16 arondessement in Paris and in a good proximity to Champs Elysee and Tour Eiffel and off course the high end mark shops. Also the staff is very friendly with good attitude. Rooms and utilities are a bit too small but it is the Parisian style. Lifts are extremely small and it is challenging to be in whit your luggage if your have big bags. WIFI is terrible. It was poor coverage and very slow which reminded me of the trips I used to make in central Africa with the same performance of Internet. Breakfast was good and had a nice variety for intercontinental breakfast.

We stayed for just one night at Melia and would recommend this hotel. The rooms were nice and clean and all staff were really friendly and welcoming. The location was convenient and we slept very well as it was so quiet. Excellent for a weekend trip.

What a lovely little hotel we arrived late and had a very friendly greeting...a quaint hotel in a good location with lovely staff. Walked across the road to a fab French restaurant. Lovely large room good amenities and once again great friendly face at check out. Good value too.

For our Honeymoon we came to Paris first for three days and we stayed here. The service was amazing. Everyone was so nice and helpful. Said checked us in and was very helpful. The roon was very clean and comfortable. We had a great view of the street. The location of the hotel was close to everything. We walked to the Eiffel Tower.

good location (metro nearby), good breakfast (with fresh orange juice), comfortable bed, coffee/tee/kettle in the room, good toiletries. Small room and very small bathroom, no slippers, no wine-bottle opener.

Can I just say that I love this hotel! 10 minutes walk from the Eifel Tower; 5 minutes walk from the Arc de Triomphe and mere minutes away from the Louvre Museum.

My wife and I were able to conveniently make all reservations for the Palace of Versailles and Dinner Cruise through the hotel resulting in a "huge" discount!

The hotel is also near some beatiful quaint little cafe's which are great for couples!

. We love the Melia brand hotels and Melia Paris Champs Elysees did not disappoint. The hotel has a great location, The Victor Hugo Metro Station is very close and is within walking distance to the Arc de Triomphe (about 10 minutes) and the Eiffel Tower (about 15-20 minutes) as well as many excellent restaurants. The room were very spacious (per European standards) and it had very comfortable beds and pillows. What really made this a great experience was the friendly and excellent staff, they go out of their way to make it a pleasant stay, especially the porter. Rooms are very clean. We had the breakfast buffet a couple of times and it was very good and a lot of variety for every palate. We will definite recommend this hotel to our friends and family and will definitely stay here next time we visit Paris.

The hotel has a great location and easily accessible to the Metro. The rooms are spacious for Paris and the bed was very comfortable. The room has all of the bathroom amenities you need.

What makes this hotel fantastic is the employees. From the moment we checked in to the time we left - we were always greeted with a warm and caring smile and you could tell they wanted to ensure all of their guests were happy. And a special thanks to Laila for all of her help.

Definitely recommend

Had two night stay recently. Excellent, small, boutique style hotel near Victor Hugo metro station. 10 minute walk to Trocadero & Eiffel Tower, but off the beaten track so feels very relaxing. Small bar & restaurant, good quality & size suite. Staff were excellent, even noticing my daughters impending birthday from her passport & leaving a note & gift in our room for her! Highly recommended & would stay again on return to Paris.

The stay was very comfortable and it was come back experience. I can recommend my friend to come and stay at Melia Paris Champs Elysees. Very convenient to Champs Elysees shopping Malls, historical places and Effiel Tower which was a five minute walk. This hotel is well situated for tourists and business people. As for me it was close to our offices.

This hotel is located at a very nice place and bro convenient around most of Paris hot spots. Rooms are not very spacious but still large enough. Reception is very helpful and attentive. Breakfast we just take around the many traditional coffeeshops.

Although the overall experience was great: good service, good smell, very clean, the rooms and elevators are Extra Small!! Don't go here with a baby, its impossible to move a small stroller around!
It was insanely small!

All the staff was very kind and helpful, very good location, good value.
The room service was not so good but correct.
The hotel is tiny but typical french.
The breakfast was good.
We recommande it for visiting Paris
